Hi, I am not able to login to confluence page..and when i am trying to recover the password, it is asking to contact the system administrtor.
Can you please help to recover my password

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-37206].
  {panel}

Add option to allow restricted Confluence pages to show in HipChat.

When CONF-30853 and CONF-31768 were fixed it broke things for folks who want restricted content to go to a private HipChat room.

I would suggest on the integrations dialogue you include a fourth checkbox for each integration to allow restricted content.

Upon double-clicking the code block macro, the code formatting will be disordered, somehow.

*Steps To reproduce*
# Create a new page.
# Add Code Block Macro with a few lines of codes, e.g.:
{noformat}
public static void main(String[] args)
{
  System.out.println("Hello World!");
}
{noformat}
# Save the page.
# Highlight the code by double clicking the code block.

Observed and Expected Behaviours are attached to this ticket. 

*Workaround*
User can opt to another browsers as a workaround, as this issue only occurs in IE.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-37197].
  {panel}

When multiple lines of codes from Code Block Macro are copied and pasted into a text editor, additional line breaks are added.

*Steps To reproduce*
# Create a new page.
# Add Code Block Macro with a few lines of codes, e.g.:
{noformat}
public static void main(String[] args)
{
  System.out.println("Hello World!");
}
{noformat}
# Save the page.
# Highlight the code and press Ctrl+C to copy code selection to clipboard.
# Press Ctrl+V to paste the clipboard contents into the Text Editor.

Observed Behaviours are attached to this ticket. 

*Workaround*
# Double click on the Code Block Macro to highlight the codes
(!) Upon double-clicking the code block macro, the code formatting will be disordered. Observed behaviour can be found in [CONF-37203|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-37203].
# Press Ctrl+C to copy code selection to clipboard.
# Press Ctrl+V to paste the clipboard contents into the Text Editor.

Besides that, user can opt to another browsers as a workaround, as this issue only occurs in IE.

